Irene Gaedie would have been proud of her daughter Kelebogile Gaedie’s matric results. The 20-year-old was among 1,300 pupils from 10 high schools in crime-ridden townships who were whisked off to a secret exam camp to write their exams under tight security. Sadly, when she collected her results, her mother was not at home to share her joy. FREE TO READ: GET THE FULL STORY IN TODAY’S TIMES SELECT